{
  "texts": [
    "Their investigation focuses on the challenges inherent on the Internet of Things.",
    "Alternatively, as demonstrated in [41,64,65], and [66], there has been a focus on the intersection of machine learning, artificial intelligence, and blockchain technology.",
    "However, a standard limitation of these studies is the need for increased practical application and empirical testing of the proposed solutions.",
    "While the potential of these technologies are deliberated in each study, empirical evidence and case studies showcasing the efficacy of machine learning and deep learning in fortifying IoT devices exist in the literature.Our survey bridges this gap by integrating these aspects, introducing novel depth to the existing literature, and paving the way to explore new research trajectories.",
    "Notably, our survey stands out by encompassing a review of the most recent articles in the field, spanning publications up to 2024."
  ]
}